  <!-- THE FORMBY BOILER PROBLEM — UNIQUE SECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">FORMBY PROPERTY KNOWLEDGE</span>
      <h2>What Most Boiler Installers Get Wrong in Formby</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">The common mistakes we see and why they matter for the specific properties and systems found across L37.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card" style="border-top:4px solid var(--red);">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">❌</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:#7f1d1d;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Fitting a standard combi in a five-bedroom Formby home</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">A 28kW or 32kW combi boiler produces hot water by heating it on demand as it passes through the heat exchanger. When two people try to shower simultaneously in a large Formby house, the flow rate drops because the boiler cannot heat enough water fast enough to serve both. The result is either a trickle of hot water or cold water entering the mix. We regularly survey L37 properties where a previous installer fitted a combi that is under-specification for the house. The fix is either a high-output combi at 36kW to 40kW or, for the largest properties, a system boiler with a hot water cylinder that stores a large volume of pre-heated water at mains pressure.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card" style="border-top:4px solid var(--red);">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">❌</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:#7f1d1d;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Working on unvented cylinders without G3 qualification</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Unvented hot water cylinders, also known as mains pressure cylinders, are common in the larger Formby properties and provide excellent simultaneous hot water flow to multiple bathrooms. However, it is illegal to install, service, repair or replace an unvented cylinder without G3 qualification. The regulation exists because an incorrectly installed unvented cylinder is a potential explosion risk. Many general plumbers and some boiler installers do not hold G3. If your current system has an unvented cylinder, verify that any installer you consider holds this qualification before they start work. All our engineers hold G3. You can check for yourself at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card" style="border-top:4px solid var(--red);">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">❌</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:#7f1d1d;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Ignoring sandy ground conditions during external pipe runs</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Formby sits on a coastal sand plain. When new boilers are installed in properties requiring new external pipe runs or where pipework is being repositioned, the sandy substrate presents different installation considerations compared to inland clay-rich soil. Pipe support and sealing at joints is more critical in sandy ground because gradual ground movement can cause stress on connections over time. We plan external pipe runs in Formby with this in mind, using appropriate pipe support and jointing techniques. It is a detail that matters over the 10 to 15 year life of a new boiler installation.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card" style="border-top:4px solid var(--green);">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <span style="font-size:1.4rem;flex-shrink:0;">✓</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:#14532d;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">What we do instead</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">We survey every Formby property in person before recommending a boiler. We check mains pressure, measure the property's hot water demand against the number of bathrooms and expected simultaneous usage, confirm whether the current cylinder is vented or unvented, and calculate the correct boiler output. We then provide a written fixed-price quote for the right system — whether that is a combi, a system boiler or a regular boiler. The free survey costs you nothing. Getting the wrong system installed costs significantly more to fix.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHAT SIZE BOILER FOR FORMBY -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Size Boiler Does My Formby Home Need?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Getting the output calculation wrong is the most common and costly boiler installation mistake. We calculate this precisely at the free survey.</p>

      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>2 to 3 bed, 1 bathroom, Formby village or Freshfield</strong><p>Smaller Formby properties — a cottage, a converted flat or a two-bedroom semi — can typically be served by a 24kW to 28kW combi boiler. A straightforward like-for-like swap at £1,800 is often the right solution.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>3 to 4 bed, 2 bathrooms, standard Formby detached</strong><p>The most common Formby property type. For a 3 to 4 bedroom home with two bathrooms, a standard 28kW to 32kW combi is frequently under-specification. We typically recommend a 36kW to 40kW combi or a system boiler with cylinder for reliable simultaneous hot water supply.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>4 to 6 bed, 3 or more bathrooms, executive Formby or Freshfield</strong><p>The larger executive homes across Formby and Freshfield need a system boiler with a properly sized unvented cylinder as the most reliable solution for multi-bathroom hot water. No combi boiler can match the simultaneous flow capacity of a well-sized system boiler and unvented cylinder combination.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Bungalows in Freshfield and Hightown</strong><p>Bungalows typically have lower hot water demand and a combi boiler is often the cleanest and most cost-effective solution. However, bungalows in Freshfield with original pipework in the roof space need particular attention to loft pipe condition before a new boiler is connected. We check this at the survey.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Signs Your Formby Boiler Needs Replacing</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">If your boiler is over 10 years old or showing any of these signs, replacement is worth considering seriously.</p>
      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Hot water is fine but pressure is poor upstairs</strong><p>In Formby's larger homes, weak hot water upstairs with a boiler that otherwise seems to be working is a strong indicator that the boiler is under-sized for the property. A new, correctly sized boiler resolves this completely. It is not a pressure problem in the mains supply — it is a boiler output problem.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler over 10 to 12 years old</strong><p>Modern A-rated condensing boilers operate at over 90% efficiency. Pre-2010 boilers typically run at 65 to 70%. The energy saving alone on a large Formby home's gas bill makes replacement cost-effective within a few years.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Unvented cylinder is over 10 years old</strong><p>Unvented cylinders have a typical life expectancy of 10 to 15 years. Key components including the expansion vessel, pressure relief valve and thermostat have shorter service lives and require replacement or inspection. We check cylinder condition and age at the free survey.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Yellow or orange boiler flame</strong><p>A healthy gas flame is blue. Yellow or orange indicates incomplete combustion and potential carbon monoxide risk. Stop using the boiler immediately. Call <a href="https://cadentgas.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999</a> if you suspect a gas emergency, then call us for assessment.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Escalating repair bills</strong><p>If annual boiler repair costs exceed £200 to £300, replacement is financially better over a 5-year horizon. A new boiler at £1,800 to £2,200 compares favourably to continued repair of an ageing unit in a Formby home that runs its heating hard over a long winter.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Benchmark or Gas Safe certificate not on record</strong><p>A boiler with no Benchmark certificate has no documented compliant installation. You have no warranty protection and limited evidence of legal installation. Replacement gives you full documentation from day one — Gas Safe certificate, Benchmark and registered manufacturer warranty.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#f97316;border-radius:10px;padding:1.5rem;text-align:center;margin-top:2rem;">
        <p style="color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Recognised two or more of these in your Formby home? Book a free survey. No obligation and no pressure.</p>
        <a href="tel:07399676656" class="btn btn-lg" style="background:#1a3a5c;color:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(26,58,92,0.4);">CALL 07399 676656</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHAT IS INCLUDED -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Is Included in Your Formby Boiler Installation</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">No hidden extras. No surprise charges. Everything included in your fully fitted price.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New boiler supplied and fitted</strong><p>Your chosen boiler from Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal or Baxi. Correctly sized through a proper output calculation at the survey. Not an estimate — an engineer's calculation based on your specific Formby property.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New unvented or vented cylinder where required</strong><p>For system boiler installations, the correct cylinder is supplied and fitted as part of the package. Unvented cylinder installations are carried out by our G3 qualified engineers only.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New smart controls and programmer</strong><p>New room thermostat and programmer installed and set up. Nest and Hive smart controls available on request. Required under <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/boiler-plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Plus regulations</a>.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Magnetic system filter</strong><p>Fitted to capture debris and magnetite. Required by Worcester Bosch and Vaillant to maintain manufacturer warranty. Non-negotiable on every installation.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>System flush and inhibitor to BS 7593 standard</strong><p>Heating system flushed and dosed with corrosion inhibitor before the new boiler is connected. Essential for protecting the new heat exchanger from day one. Particularly important for older Formby properties with accumulated debris.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas Safe and Benchmark certificates on the day</strong><p>Legal requirement. Both issued on installation day and sent by email. Required to validate the manufacturer warranty.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Manufacturer warranty registered on your behalf</strong><p>We register with Worcester Bosch or Vaillant on installation day. You receive email confirmation. Warranty registration is frequently forgotten and when it is, you lose protection from day one.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Old boiler removed. Full commissioning and demonstration.</strong><p>Old boiler and associated waste removed. New system fully commissioned, radiators balanced, pressure set. Full heating and hot water cycle run. We walk you through new controls before we leave.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- BRANDS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Boiler Brands We Install in Formby</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">We install the four most trusted brands in the UK. All A-rated condensing boilers compliant with Boiler Plus regulations.</p>
      <div class="pf-why-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-why-item" style="position:relative;">
          <div style="position:absolute;top:-12px;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);background:#f97316;color:#ffffff;font-size:0.68rem;font-weight:800;padding:0.2rem 0.75rem;border-radius:999px;white-space:nowrap;letter-spacing:0.05em;">OUR PRIMARY RECOMMENDATION</div>
          <h3>Worcester Bosch</h3>
          <p>The most reliable boiler brand in the UK per <a href="https://www.which.co.uk/reviews/boilers/article/best-boiler-brands" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Which?</a>. The Greenstar system boiler range is particularly well suited to Formby's larger properties. Up to 10-year warranty when installed by an accredited engineer and serviced annually. Greenstar system boilers pair exceptionally with unvented cylinders for multi-bathroom homes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-why-item">
          <h3>Vaillant</h3>
          <p>Premium German engineering. One of the quietest and most efficient boilers available. The ecoTEC system range is an outstanding choice for larger Formby properties that value low noise alongside high efficiency. Up to 10-year warranty. Particularly well regarded in high-end residential properties across L37 and Freshfield.</p>
        </div>
