      <h2>Boiler Installation Formby. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Formby homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">SYSTEM BOILER</span>&nbsp; Do I need a system boiler rather than a combi in my Formby home?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Frequently yes. For a Formby home with two or more bathrooms and multiple people showering at different times, a standard combi boiler is typically under-specification. A system boiler with a properly sized hot water cylinder provides simultaneous high-pressure hot water to multiple outlets without any compromise. We calculate the correct approach at the free survey based on your specific property and bathroom count.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">G3</span>&nbsp; Why does G3 qualification matter for my Formby property?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>G3 is the mandatory qualification for working on unvented hot water cylinders. Unvented cylinders are common in Formby's larger properties and provide excellent mains pressure hot water to multiple bathrooms. It is illegal to install, service or replace an unvented cylinder without G3 qualification. Many general plumbers and some boiler companies do not hold it. All our engineers do. Verify this by checking at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does a new boiler cost in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A like-for-like combi boiler installation starts from £1,800 fully fitted. System boilers from £2,200. Regular boilers from £2,500. For Formby properties, a system boiler installation is very commonly the right choice and represents better long-term value than an under-sized combi. Written fixed-price quote after the free survey. No surprises on invoice day.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">TIME</span>&nbsp; How long does a boiler installation take in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A like-for-like combi replacement takes 4 to 6 hours in one day. A system boiler with new cylinder installation takes 1 to 2 days depending on complexity. Multi-zone systems in larger Freshfield or executive Formby properties may take 2 to 3 days. We confirm the exact duration at the free survey.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">WARRANTY</span>&nbsp; What warranty does a new Formby boiler installation carry?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Worcester Bosch and Vaillant offer up to 10-year warranties when installed by an accredited engineer and serviced annually. Ideal and Baxi offer between 5 and 10 years depending on the model. All our installations carry a 12-month workmanship guarantee. We register the manufacturer warranty on installation day. Annual servicing is required to keep the warranty valid — see our <a href="/boiler-service-formby">boiler service Formby page</a>.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for Formby boiler installations?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All our engineers are Gas Safe registered. Verify our registration at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. Gas Safe and Benchmark certificates are issued on installation day for every job. It is illegal to install a gas boiler without Gas Safe registration.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">HEAT PUMP</span>&nbsp; Should I consider a heat pump for my Formby property?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>For larger Formby detached properties with gardens, a heat pump may be worth exploring. The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-boiler-upgrade-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Upgrade Scheme</a> provides grants of up to £7,500 toward heat pump installation. Suitability depends on your property's insulation levels, available outdoor space and existing heating distribution. We advise on suitability at the free survey. Not all Formby properties are heat pump candidates, and we will tell you clearly if your home is not suited.</p></div></details>
